1
00:00:26,660 --> 00:00:27,220
(Loading)

2
00:00:27,220 --> 00:00:29,700
(Dungeon Pass)

3
00:00:30,180 --> 00:00:31,900
(Truth Inn)

4
00:00:34,780 --> 00:00:35,980
(The Truth)

5
00:00:36,900 --> 00:00:41,060
=The Truth (Season 4)=

6
00:00:41,460 --> 00:00:42,320
(All persons, backgrounds,
and descriptions are fictional.)

7
00:00:42,320 --> 00:00:42,970
(Settings and actions are setups.)

8
00:00:42,970 --> 00:00:43,400
(All photos and videos)

9
00:00:43,400 --> 00:00:43,900
(are authorized.)

10
00:00:43,900 --> 00:00:44,690
(Safety measures were taken
during shooting. Don't try this at home.)

11
00:00:44,690 --> 00:00:45,230
(Parental supervision required
for underage viewers.)

12
00:00:45,240 --> 00:00:45,620
(Enter game.)

13
00:00:45,640 --> 00:00:47,720
(Previous episode)
Chancellor Tui invited us to a banquet.

14
00:00:48,320 --> 00:00:49,200
Someone help!

15
00:00:49,200 --> 00:00:50,820
Chancellor Tui is dead!

16
00:00:50,840 --> 00:00:51,320
You're...

17
00:00:51,680 --> 00:00:52,800
(Ning Waver, Young Commander)
from the Li Kingdom!

18
00:00:52,800 --> 00:00:54,640
I'm actually that little brother
of yours.

19
00:00:54,660 --> 00:00:55,860
(Yang Glory,
Founder of Thousand-Faced Eagle King)

20
00:00:56,040 --> 00:00:57,120
Ke Stubborn!

21
00:00:57,120 --> 00:00:57,760
You...

22
00:00:57,760 --> 00:00:59,520
(A Tui Kingdom big shot)
He framed the Longdong Army.

23
00:00:59,520 --> 00:01:02,200
(Ke Stubborn, Kuang's top Shadow Guard)
I'm the princess' top Shadow Guard.

24
00:01:02,200 --> 00:01:03,160
(Jin Thrifty, Princess of Kuang)
Show some respect.

25
00:01:03,160 --> 00:01:05,640
(He Ha, Crown Prince of Tui)
I want to kill He Ha.

26
00:01:05,640 --> 00:01:06,400
Crown Prince of Tui,

27
00:01:06,400 --> 00:01:07,280
why did you suddenly

28
00:01:07,280 --> 00:01:08,160
(Ding Pillar, Crown Prince of Li)
attack me?

29
00:01:08,160 --> 00:01:10,080
The person
who started that war wasn't me.

30
00:01:10,080 --> 00:01:11,040
The real culprit...

31
00:01:11,640 --> 00:01:12,280
was him.

32
00:01:12,280 --> 00:01:13,800
Ke Stubborn...

33
00:01:13,800 --> 00:01:15,800
(All four are dead)
I'm dead?

34
00:01:15,800 --> 00:01:17,360
I'm the only one alive.

35
00:01:17,860 --> 00:01:19,340
(Night vision mode)

36
00:01:19,400 --> 00:01:20,640
Go!

37
00:01:20,640 --> 00:01:21,520
Open it.

38
00:01:21,520 --> 00:01:22,360
Get in, quick!

39
00:01:22,360 --> 00:01:23,640
We've blocked it off.

40
00:01:23,640 --> 00:01:25,400
That was awesome.

41
00:01:25,700 --> 00:01:29,020
(Mourning)

42
00:01:34,840 --> 00:01:35,480
What's this?

43
00:01:37,240 --> 00:01:38,520
Where are we?

44
00:01:38,520 --> 00:01:39,600
What's going on outside?

45
00:01:40,040 --> 00:01:40,880
Smoke?

46
00:01:40,880 --> 00:01:41,480
Look outside.

47
00:01:43,760 --> 00:01:45,080
(Mass graveyard)
Those are graves.

48
00:01:45,080 --> 00:01:45,760
A mass graveyard.

49
00:01:46,140 --> 00:01:49,260
(New scene unlocked: Mass Graveyard)

50
00:01:53,740 --> 00:01:56,260
(Grave of the Nameless)

51
00:02:01,580 --> 00:02:03,900
(Junzi Ruyu, Yan Reason)

52
00:02:05,040 --> 00:02:08,600
Yan Reason and Junzi Ruyu?

53
00:02:08,600 --> 00:02:10,820
(Why are Yan Reason
and Junzi Ruyu locked up here?)

54
00:02:10,840 --> 00:02:13,080
You two finally ended up together.

55
00:02:13,080 --> 00:02:14,200
(Focusing on what really matters)

56
00:02:14,200 --> 00:02:14,720
Ke.

57
00:02:15,040 --> 00:02:16,280
There are the blue and red buffs.

58
00:02:16,680 --> 00:02:17,720
(Memories from a past life)
Blue and red buffs.

59
00:02:17,720 --> 00:02:18,480
Blue buff.

60
00:02:18,480 --> 00:02:20,060
(Jungler instincts awakened)
Finish them off.

61
00:02:20,080 --> 00:02:21,120
Ke!

62
00:02:21,520 --> 00:02:22,200
Save us!

63
00:02:22,200 --> 00:02:23,680
Girl, help us.

64
00:02:26,100 --> 00:02:32,420
(This fictional story
contains horror elements)

65
00:02:32,440 --> 00:02:33,960
Why are there ghost soldiers here too?

66
00:02:34,120 --> 00:02:35,480
Open the door!

67
00:02:38,800 --> 00:02:39,880
There are more behind us!

68
00:02:40,360 --> 00:02:40,800
Open it!

69
00:02:41,040 --> 00:02:43,160
No, it won't open.
We have to squeeze through.

70
00:02:45,180 --> 00:02:45,940
Push!

71
00:02:46,420 --> 00:02:47,180
Push!

72
00:02:47,840 --> 00:02:49,080
Push!

73
00:02:52,200 --> 00:02:52,880
Go!

74
00:02:52,880 --> 00:02:53,160
Push!

75
00:02:53,160 --> 00:02:53,920
Hurry!

76
00:02:55,080 --> 00:02:56,740
Get in, Ke! Hurry!

77
00:02:58,040 --> 00:03:00,420
(Calmly covering their retreat)
It's fine. I'm used to this.

78
00:03:04,280 --> 00:03:05,120
Block it!

79
00:03:05,120 --> 00:03:05,600
Use that to block it!

80
00:03:05,600 --> 00:03:06,400
Push it over and block the entrance!

81
00:03:11,300 --> 00:03:12,500
(Ghost soldiers successfully blocked)

82
00:03:12,520 --> 00:03:13,680
You're using us as a barricade?

83
00:03:13,680 --> 00:03:15,060
(Red and blue buffs stand guard)

84
00:03:15,240 --> 00:03:16,680
You two stay in there for now.

85
00:03:16,680 --> 00:03:17,680
We need the extra weight.

86
00:03:17,680 --> 00:03:18,920
Help me!

87
00:03:18,920 --> 00:03:19,440
Ke!

88
00:03:19,640 --> 00:03:20,840
Let's rescue them first.

89
00:03:20,840 --> 00:03:21,780
(Can always count on Ning)

90
00:03:22,200 --> 00:03:23,400
Where's the key?

91
00:03:23,400 --> 00:03:25,300
(Searching for the prison cart key)

92
00:03:31,120 --> 00:03:32,560
Can we use this dustpan as a shield?

93
00:03:32,560 --> 00:03:33,120
Give them a whack.

94
00:03:33,220 --> 00:03:33,620
(Ghost soldiers)

95
00:03:34,020 --> 00:03:35,120
(Forcing a path through)

96
00:03:35,120 --> 00:03:35,440
They...

97
00:03:35,440 --> 00:03:36,800
Do you know where the key is?

98
00:03:36,800 --> 00:03:37,420
(The solution must be nearby)

99
00:03:38,020 --> 00:03:39,660
(You wouldn't get it)

100
00:03:42,080 --> 00:03:42,800
Here's the key!

101
00:03:42,800 --> 00:03:44,180
(Prison cart key)

102
00:03:45,300 --> 00:03:46,940
(Prison cart key)

103
00:03:46,960 --> 00:03:47,680
Found it.

104
00:03:47,880 --> 00:03:48,720
Let's unlock it.

105
00:03:48,720 --> 00:03:49,440
Unlock it.

106
00:03:50,800 --> 00:03:51,800
We'll get you out first.

107
00:03:51,800 --> 00:03:52,880
Thank goodness.

108
00:03:52,880 --> 00:03:53,920
We've been locked up for five days.

109
00:03:54,320 --> 00:03:55,920
Five days?

110
00:03:55,920 --> 00:03:57,800
And you haven't lost any weight.

111
00:03:58,160 --> 00:03:59,120
You must be thrilled.

112
00:04:00,100 --> 00:04:00,940
(Bro, you get me)

113
00:04:04,440 --> 00:04:05,120
All right, come on.

114
00:04:05,120 --> 00:04:06,160
Thank you.

115
00:04:07,440 --> 00:04:08,640
You've got new shoes again?

116
00:04:08,920 --> 00:04:10,120
Girl,

117
00:04:10,120 --> 00:04:11,240
you're finally out.

118
00:04:11,240 --> 00:04:12,320
Are your shoes okay?

119
00:04:12,320 --> 00:04:14,160
Junzi gave me another pair.

120
00:04:14,720 --> 00:04:15,520
There's a bee!

121
00:04:15,520 --> 00:04:16,880
You mustn't hit bees.

122
00:04:17,800 --> 00:04:18,880
I don't believe that.

123
00:04:18,880 --> 00:04:19,680
(Rebellious)
Why can't I hit it?

124
00:04:19,680 --> 00:04:21,200
The queen bee will come after you.

125
00:04:21,200 --> 00:04:22,070
(Tui Kingdom folk belief)

126
00:04:22,070 --> 00:04:23,440
The queen bee will come for you.

127
00:04:23,440 --> 00:04:24,580
(Stay away from ghost soldiers and bees)
Let's go.

128
00:04:24,760 --> 00:04:25,760
This door is

129
00:04:25,760 --> 00:04:26,840
our only way out.

130
00:04:26,840 --> 00:04:27,600
The only one?

131
00:04:27,600 --> 00:04:27,920
Yes.

132
00:04:27,920 --> 00:04:29,520
(Only exit)
It's our only escape route.

133
00:04:29,520 --> 00:04:31,040
But two people must stand over there

134
00:04:31,040 --> 00:04:31,640
and press the buttons together

135
00:04:32,080 --> 00:04:33,510
(Both switches must be pressed)
to open the door.

136
00:04:33,600 --> 00:04:35,120
Press them at the same time?

137
00:04:35,440 --> 00:04:36,320
Once you let go,

138
00:04:36,320 --> 00:04:37,320
the switches stop working.

139
00:04:37,340 --> 00:04:38,120
(Warning: The switches
can only be used once)

140
00:04:38,120 --> 00:04:40,160
(Letting go will close the exit)
The gate holding them back will open.

141
00:04:40,560 --> 00:04:42,280
The ones pressing the buttons
have to dash out,

142
00:04:42,280 --> 00:04:43,760
and we only get one chance.

143
00:04:44,020 --> 00:04:45,540
(How can everyone escape
before the door closes?)

144
00:04:45,680 --> 00:04:46,720
Then you two should do it.

145
00:04:47,000 --> 00:04:47,860
(You two)
Okay.

146
00:04:47,880 --> 00:04:49,320
Junzi Ruyu, ever since I was little,

147
00:04:49,320 --> 00:04:50,600
mentor has always said

148
00:04:51,120 --> 00:04:53,000
that you're highly skilled
in martial arts.

149
00:04:53,000 --> 00:04:54,600
You even fought
in a martial contest for marriage,

150
00:04:54,600 --> 00:04:56,600
(A convincing argument)
so you must be good.

151
00:04:56,600 --> 00:04:57,960
But we have clues.

152
00:04:57,960 --> 00:04:59,000
Don't you want them?

153
00:04:59,440 --> 00:05:00,400
Tell us first,

154
00:05:00,400 --> 00:05:01,040
then go press the buttons.

155
00:05:01,040 --> 00:05:01,800
(Unfazed by the pressure)

156
00:05:01,800 --> 00:05:03,800
We'll only tell you somewhere well-lit.

157
00:05:03,800 --> 00:05:06,040
Looks like only the two of us

158
00:05:06,040 --> 00:05:07,760
(Shadow Guard, General, Crown Prince)
are strong enough for the job.

159
00:05:07,760 --> 00:05:08,800
(A task for the strong)
Only the two of us?

160
00:05:08,800 --> 00:05:09,280
Yeah.

161
00:05:09,400 --> 00:05:10,840
One has an injured hand,
the other an injured leg.

162
00:05:11,180 --> 00:05:12,500
(Battle-worn crown prince)

163
00:05:12,840 --> 00:05:13,520
Here's the problem.

164
00:05:13,520 --> 00:05:14,880
They might come out and block us.

165
00:05:14,880 --> 00:05:15,840
That's what we're worried about.

166
00:05:16,400 --> 00:05:16,720
Yeah.

167
00:05:16,720 --> 00:05:17,420
(Ghost soldiers may block the way)

168
00:05:17,460 --> 00:05:20,340
(But everyone must succeed
on the first try to escape)

169
00:05:20,420 --> 00:05:21,660
The Freeze Card!

170
00:05:21,700 --> 00:05:22,440
(Sibling telepathy)

171
00:05:22,440 --> 00:05:23,200
Okay, come on.

172
00:05:23,440 --> 00:05:24,400
Quick, just run!

173
00:05:24,400 --> 00:05:24,920
(Just charge ahead)
It'll be quick.

174
00:05:24,920 --> 00:05:25,560
Wait... Fine.

175
00:05:25,560 --> 00:05:27,080
Alright, you two press the buttons.

176
00:05:27,080 --> 00:05:28,360
(Us?)

177
00:05:28,360 --> 00:05:29,440
People always say

178
00:05:29,440 --> 00:05:31,440
it's not very gentlemanly
to make women do this.

179
00:05:31,440 --> 00:05:33,320
(Doing the exact opposite)
Let's throw chivalry out the window.

180
00:05:33,560 --> 00:05:34,800
We'll do the exact opposite.

181
00:05:35,240 --> 00:05:36,320
Fine, we'll do it.

182
00:05:36,320 --> 00:05:36,640
Let's go.

183
00:05:37,080 --> 00:05:37,840
Seriously?

184
00:05:38,240 --> 00:05:38,880
Don't!

185
00:05:38,880 --> 00:05:40,320
(Princess, you mustn't!)
It's too dangerous!

186
00:05:40,320 --> 00:05:41,600
If the two of you

187
00:05:41,600 --> 00:05:42,920
save the four of us,

188
00:05:42,920 --> 00:05:44,120
you'll truly be...

189
00:05:44,780 --> 00:05:46,300
Great heroines.

190
00:05:46,700 --> 00:05:47,980
(Flattered into agreeing)

191
00:05:48,200 --> 00:05:48,920
Which one do we press?

192
00:05:48,920 --> 00:05:49,400
This one.

193
00:05:49,840 --> 00:05:51,320
Wait.

194
00:05:51,320 --> 00:05:52,480
Are we really doing this?

195
00:05:52,680 --> 00:05:53,200
It's okay.

196
00:05:53,200 --> 00:05:53,840
(Let's do it)
Hurry up.

197
00:05:53,840 --> 00:05:54,680
I was only joking.

198
00:05:54,680 --> 00:05:56,640
(Sharp tongue, soft heart)
Come on, let's try it.

199
00:05:56,640 --> 00:05:57,400
I was kidding.

200
00:05:57,400 --> 00:05:58,680
I already believe you're great heroines.

201
00:05:58,680 --> 00:05:59,520
(Title bestowed by Young General Dong)
The title is yours.

202
00:05:59,520 --> 00:06:00,480
Come on. Let's go.

203
00:06:01,080 --> 00:06:02,160
What a shame, Jin.

204
00:06:02,160 --> 00:06:02,860
(Her heroine dream shattered)

205
00:06:03,120 --> 00:06:03,840
Seriously.

206
00:06:03,840 --> 00:06:04,600
All right, everyone. Get out.

207
00:06:06,100 --> 00:06:07,460
(Both switches activated)

208
00:06:08,560 --> 00:06:09,120
It's open.

209
00:06:09,120 --> 00:06:09,740
(The exit is open)

210
00:06:10,380 --> 00:06:12,500
(The ghost soldiers begin to stir)

211
00:06:12,500 --> 00:06:14,260
(The other four have reached the exit)

212
00:06:15,560 --> 00:06:16,400
Let's go, Ning.

213
00:06:16,400 --> 00:06:18,100
(Letting go will close the exit
and release the ghost soldiers)

214
00:06:18,640 --> 00:06:18,840
Ready.

215
00:06:19,520 --> 00:06:20,880
Three, two, one!

216
00:06:28,640 --> 00:06:29,320
Come on!

217
00:06:37,760 --> 00:06:38,440
Hurry!

218
00:06:42,300 --> 00:06:43,580
(A ghost soldier suddenly flashes over)
Wait!

219
00:06:45,020 --> 00:06:46,120
(Only Ke Stubborn escaped)
Wait!

220
00:06:46,120 --> 00:06:46,760
Ning!

221
00:06:46,760 --> 00:06:47,880
(Passage blocked)

222
00:06:47,880 --> 00:06:48,600
Wait!

223
00:06:49,520 --> 00:06:50,200
Hurry!

224
00:06:50,200 --> 00:06:51,340
(Trapped on both sides)

225
00:06:51,340 --> 00:06:52,620
(The exit is about to close)

226
00:06:54,000 --> 00:06:55,120
Freeze Card!

227
00:06:55,120 --> 00:06:56,240
Use the Freeze Card!

228
00:06:56,240 --> 00:06:57,800
Three, two, one! Freeze Card!

229
00:06:57,800 --> 00:07:00,660
(Freeze Card)

230
00:07:04,980 --> 00:07:06,620
(The exit cannot be frozen)

231
00:07:08,200 --> 00:07:08,880
Ning, hurry!

232
00:07:08,880 --> 00:07:09,280
Ning!

233
00:07:09,280 --> 00:07:10,400
Freeze the door too!

234
00:07:10,400 --> 00:07:11,460
(The Freeze Card only works on NPCs)

235
00:07:13,640 --> 00:07:14,440
Ning!

236
00:07:18,200 --> 00:07:18,880
We made it.

237
00:07:19,860 --> 00:07:22,780
(Finally safe)

238
00:07:22,800 --> 00:07:24,440
A few days ago, my companions and I

239
00:07:24,440 --> 00:07:25,720
came here to rescue a child.

240
00:07:26,240 --> 00:07:27,920
They took the child to the Ghost Market.

241
00:07:28,320 --> 00:07:29,080
I stayed behind

242
00:07:29,080 --> 00:07:30,240
and was trapped here

243
00:07:30,240 --> 00:07:31,640
until Junzi rescued me.

244
00:07:31,640 --> 00:07:31,960
Right.

245
00:07:32,200 --> 00:07:32,920
Who captured her?

246
00:07:33,680 --> 00:07:34,640
Chancellor Tui.

247
00:07:35,000 --> 00:07:36,720
Chancellor Tui is a treacherous villain.

248
00:07:37,360 --> 00:07:38,640
He murders innocent people

249
00:07:39,080 --> 00:07:41,360
and controls them
using some strange method.

250
00:07:41,360 --> 00:07:43,060
(A strange method
of controlling the living)

251
00:07:43,280 --> 00:07:44,480
I thought I'd never escape,

252
00:07:44,480 --> 00:07:46,160
so I sewed the evidence into my clothes.

253
00:07:46,480 --> 00:07:47,040
Here.

254
00:07:47,040 --> 00:07:48,080
(Piece of clothing)
Okay, understood.

255
00:07:48,080 --> 00:07:49,560
You must expose his plot.

256
00:07:49,560 --> 00:07:50,040
We will.

257
00:07:50,040 --> 00:07:50,720
Give the people justice.

258
00:07:51,220 --> 00:07:52,260
(Leave it to us)

259
00:07:53,560 --> 00:07:55,480
Junzi Ruyu, can I have the fan?

260
00:07:56,240 --> 00:07:56,840
You're sweating.

261
00:07:58,080 --> 00:07:58,600
Thank you.

262
00:07:58,600 --> 00:07:59,120
Give me one too.

263
00:08:00,640 --> 00:08:01,560
Thanks.

264
00:08:05,200 --> 00:08:07,080
A little dirt on Chancellor Tui?

265
00:08:07,080 --> 00:08:08,920
(A Little Dirt on Chancellor Tui)

266
00:08:08,920 --> 00:08:09,680
This folding fan

267
00:08:10,400 --> 00:08:11,120
was found

268
00:08:11,120 --> 00:08:12,640
at Lord Tui's manor.

269
00:08:12,640 --> 00:08:14,240
(The fan was found at Chivalry Manor)
It contains

270
00:08:14,640 --> 00:08:15,720
all kinds of dirt on Chancellor Tui.

271
00:08:15,720 --> 00:08:16,480
Study it carefully.

272
00:08:16,920 --> 00:08:17,800
Read it when we get back.

273
00:08:18,080 --> 00:08:19,520
And...

274
00:08:19,520 --> 00:08:19,960
there's also...

275
00:08:20,580 --> 00:08:21,860
(Rummaging)

276
00:08:22,240 --> 00:08:23,480
We probably don't need this.

277
00:08:23,760 --> 00:08:24,400
It smells a little.

278
00:08:25,840 --> 00:08:26,360
What is it?

279
00:08:26,960 --> 00:08:29,640
Since you
founded the Thousand-Faced Eagle King,

280
00:08:29,640 --> 00:08:32,120
it's only right
that I return this to you.

281
00:08:32,120 --> 00:08:33,550
Just say the password.

